<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17189] camel-salesforce forcably overrides the httpclient from SalesforceEndpointConfig</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17189</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The comment here seems to imply that there should be a way to manually create an HttpClient in SalesforceEndpointConfig: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/main/components/camel-salesforce/camel-salesforce-component/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/salesforce/SalesforceComponent.java#L452&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/blob/main/components/camel-salesforce/camel-salesforce-component/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/salesforce/SalesforceComponent.java#L452&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, in reality, the doStart method always overrides the value provided by the configuration without first checking whether or not the config already has an HttpClient configured.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seems to be a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
